        <briefdescription>
<para>Create a delay instance. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Allocates a dual-buffer circular delay line of length num_taps. The internal buffer is rounded up to the next power of two for efficient modular addressing.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>num_taps</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Window length (&gt;= 1). Rounded up internally. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Heap-allocated state, or NULL on allocation failure. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Caller must call <ref refid="delay__core_8h_1af86697e7770441aa91a811feb6b5e9c3" kindref="member">delay_destroy()</ref> when done. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
